Using cmake:
$ cmake .
$ make

pythonX.Y-config --cflags will give you the recommended flags when compiling:

$ /usr/bin/python2.7-config --cflags

pythonX.Y-config --ldflags will give you the recommended flags when linking:

$ python2.7-config --ldflags
-lpthread -ldl -lutil -lm -lpython2.7 -Xlinker -export-dynamic

Using call_function:
$ ./call_function py_function multiply
$ ./call_function py_function multiply1 3 5
$ ./call_class py_class Multiply multiply
$ ./call_class py_class Multiply multiply2 8 4
$ ./call_thread py_thread ThreadFunc
$ ./call_thread py_thread createThread
$ ./call_thread_2 py_thread MyThread run
